node.text:
Air Astana Is Giving ‘Serious Thought’ To Dedicated Freighter Aircraft ⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Air Astana is giving serious thought to dedicated freighter operations, as it is converting its makeshift Boeing 767 freighter back into a passenger aircraft. The airline’s CEO Peter Foster told Simple Flying that the decision is complicated as returning passenger capacity could lead to a ‘glut’ of cargo capacity.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Air Astana⁠
⁠

node.text:
Alaska Airlines Boeing 737 Evacuated After Phone Catches Fire⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
On August 23rd, an Alaska Airlines flight from Louis Armstrong New Orleans International Airport (MSY) to Seattle Tacoma International (SEA) experienced a cell phone fire onboard leading to the deployment of the aircraft’s evacuation slides. The 737-900ER operating flight AS751 had touched down in Seattle when the incident occurred.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠
⁠

node.text:
Wow: The Boeing 777X Gives Impressive Golf Tournament Flyover⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Boeing closed the Boeing Classic golf tournament with a spectacular flyover, performed by its flagship new widebody, the 777X. WH001, Boeing’s first 777-9, stunned the crowds at the event, performing a figure of eight in the skies above the course.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠

node.text:
Travel Chaos? Icelandic Air Traffic Control Strike Planned Next Week⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
A meeting yesterday between unions and airport management in Iceland didn’t end in a satisfactory resolution. As such, Air Traffic Controllers at Iceland’s Keflavík Airport will go on strike next week. The planned strike action will take place on August 31st and will impact thousands of passengers.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠
⁠

node.text:
Breaking: Delta Ups Airbus A321neo Order To 155 Aircraft⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Delta has increased its Airbus A321 order commitments by 30 aircraft. The airline now has 155 outstanding orders for aircraft from Airbus' popular A321neo family, as the aircraft comes in addition to an existing firm order for 125 planes of the type.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠

node.text:
Europe’s Busiest Airport: A Week In The Operations Of Amsterdam Schiphol⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Amsterdam Schiphol was Europe’s busiest airport by total flights operated in the week to August 23rd, Eurocontrol confirms. It had 10,722 movements – across airlines, bizjets, any military – in the seven-day period. We examine Schiphol’s passenger airlines and network that week.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠

node.text:
Afghanistan Airlift: Lufthansa Has Flown Over 1,500 In One Week⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
During its first week of assisting the Afghanistan evacuation effort, Lufthansa has flown more than 1,500 individuals from Tashkent in Uzbekistan to Frankfurt, Germany. The individuals transported have previously been flown out of Afghanistan by the German armed forces (Bundeswehr).⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Bundeswehr⁠
⁠

node.text:
Longer Flight Paths Force Air India To Reduce Payload On US Flights⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
As Afghan airspace remains off-limits to commercial flights, Air India has been feeling the impact. In order to service its US routes, the carrier has had to reduce its total payload to accommodate more fuel. This has meant offloading baggage and valuable cargo to make the longer journey. Let’s find out more.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠

node.text:
Sydney Airport’s Sale – What Is The Latest?⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
The board of Australia’s busiest commercial airport has rejected a US$21.4 billion takeover bid, saying the offer does not reflect the airport’s true value. Sydney Airport is Australia’s only publicly listed airport. However, a consortium of institutional investors wants to take the airport private.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Getty Images⁠

node.text:
Southwest To Help Fly Afghan Refugees Around The US⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
Starting Monday, low-cost carrier Southwest will operate a series of flights chartered by the Pentagon. The airline will assist in transporting refugees and evacuees from Afghanistan to undisclosed domestic locations. Southwest says it is proud to be a part of the military’s humanitarian airlift mission and stands ready to provide additional support if needed.⁠
⁠
🛬 For the most recent up to date news, google 'Simple Flying.' 🛬⁠
⁠
Photo Source: Vincenzo Pace | Simple Flying | @jfkjetsofficial⁠

Virgin’s 747 Satellite Launch Company Set To Become Public⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠

⁠

What Is The United States Civil Reserve Air Fleet?⁠
⁠
✈️ For the full story, visit the link in our bio. ✈️⁠
⁠
The United States Department of Defense (DOD) formally announced yesterday that it would activate Stage I of the Civil Reserve Air Fleet (CRAF) to help with the Afghanistan evacuations. With this critical action taking place, let’s take a look at CRAF’s role.⁠
⁠
